# parallel-agent-swarm-dispatch-patterns — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-05-28)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus 9-issue Myrmidon swarm session (2026-05-28)
**Verification:** verified-local (6 PRs merged, main green, 762 automation tests pass — process/orchestration learning, not CI-gated code change)

### What changed

- Added **Part 10** — Orchestrator Pre-Dispatch Re-Grade Gate (new section in Verified Workflow)
- Added delegation-shim-ratio heuristic table (≥50% shims = DONE-ALREADY, 25–49% = PARTIAL, <25% = KEEP)
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows (28, 29, 30): CI matrix already-done, shim-ratio dispatch avoidance, plan-reviewer self-review non-convergence
- Added 2 new "When to Use" bullet points for pre-dispatch re-grade and God-Class shim-ratio evaluation
- Updated description to add trigger (8): re-grading a batch of GitHub issues against CURRENT repo state
- Added 8 new tags: `pre-dispatch-regrade`, `delegation-shim-ratio`, `already-done-classification`, `moot-churn`, `god-class-decomposition`, `orchestrator-gate`
- Added ProjectHephaestus 2026-05-28 row to Verified On table
- Updated Overview Outcome paragraph with v1.1.0 summary
- Bumped version 1.0.0 → 1.1.0, date 2026-05-19 → 2026-05-28

### Why

Part 8 (stop-and-reassess gate) covered between-phases re-grade, but no section covered the
orchestrator-level pre-dispatch re-grade — checking every issue against CURRENT code before
dispatching any agent. Of 9 ProjectHephaestus issues: #539 was fully resolved (grep returned
no matches), #468 was effectively decomposed (shim ratio 21/40 = 52.5% — all 6 named
responsibilities already extracted), and #614 was only partial (scaffolding present, break not
wired). Without the pre-dispatch gate, an orchestrator would dispatch moot implementation agents
causing churn with regression risk against a live automation pipeline. Also capturing the
plan-reviewer self-review non-convergence bug (issue #671).

### Previous version (v1.0.0) snapshot

See "Superseded from tooling-myrmidon-swarm-prompt-guardrails-reduce-stall-rate" section below
for v1.0.0 content. The v1.0.0 consolidated skill had 9 parts (Part 1–9), 27 Failed Attempts rows,
and was verified across ProjectScylla, ProjectArgus, ProjectAgamemnon, Myrmidons, and ProjectMnemosyne.

